  "description": "Anders Birger Bohlin was a Swedish teacher and paleontologist born in 1898 in Lidköping. He graduated from Strängnäs in 1916 and from Uppsala University with a Bachelor's degree in 1922, a Master's degree in 1926, and a PhD in 1935, all in the field of paleontology. Between 1934-1944, he was a docent in paleontology and later became a teacher in biology, health science, and chemistry at Halmstad starting in 1944. Bohlin traveled to various European countries, the US, and China between 1927-1933 and assisted in excavations in Chow-K'ou-Tien. He authored around 30 scientific articles about fossil vertebrates and was awarded the Royal Order of the North Star."
